summary:
The Security Council:

Recalling its previous resolutions on Libya, including 1970 (2011), 2259 (2015), 2510 (2020), 2542 (2020), and 2570 (2021),

Recalling its determination that the situation in Libya continues to threaten international peace and security,

1. Decides to extend the mandate of the United Nations Support Mission in Libya (UNSMIL) until 30 April 2022, as an integrated special political mission to carry out its mandate as set out in resolutions 2542 (2020) and 2570 (2021);

2. Recalls that UNSMIL should be led by a Special Envoy and recognizes the Secretary-General's responsibility to appoint a Special Envoy as set out in resolution 2542 (2020);

3. Decides to remain actively seized of the matter.
